# Frontend conventions

## Structure

- Pages live in `src/app/`. Each route segment uses Next.js conventions (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`).
- Reusable UI primitives are in `src/components/ui/` (shadcn/ui) and `src/components/ds/` (Tenantly DS).
- Feature modules live under `src/features/<domain>/` with `components/`, `hooks/`, `actions/` (server actions), and `schemas.ts`.
- Web-only helpers (next/navigation wrappers, browser-only utils) live in `src/lib/`.

## Server vs Client components

- Default to **Server Components**.
- Add `'use client'` only when you need: hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, etc.), event handlers, browser APIs, or third-party client-only libs.
- Never read secrets in a client component. Read on the server, pass minimal data down.

## Data fetching

- Server Components: fetch directly via Supabase server helper or Route Handler call.
- Client Components: TanStack Query hooks from `src/core/queries/`.
- Mutations: TanStack Query `useMutation` invalidating relevant query keys.
- Realtime: subscribe via Supabase Realtime channels; integrate with Query cache via `setQueryData`.

## Forms

- React Hook Form + Zod resolver.
- Zod schemas live in `src/core/schemas/<entity>.ts` (portable).
- Submit handlers call mutation hooks; never raw fetch.

## Styling

- Tailwind v4 with project tokens (`oklch(...)` CSS variables in `src/styles/globals.css`).
- shadcn/ui primitives + Tenantly DS layer for higher-level patterns (PageHeader, DataTable, StatusBadge, BottomSheet).
- No inline styles unless dynamic.
- Mobile-first; use `md:` / `lg:` for breakpoints.

## State

- **Server state** → TanStack Query.
- **UI state (modals, drawers, transient selections)** → Zustand stores in `src/core/stores/` (must remain portable).
- **Form state** → React Hook Form.
- **Active context** → `useActiveContext()` hook reading the URL.

## Routing & layouts

- Use route groups: `(landlord)`, `(tenant)`, `(admin)`, `(auth)`, `(public)`.
- URL prefix is the source of truth for active context — `/landlord/{slug}/...`, `/tenant/...`, `/admin/...`.
- Layout-level membership checks via Server Component layout files.

## Performance

- Lazy-load non-critical features with `dynamic()`.
- Use `next/image` for all images.
- Use `next/font/google` with variable fonts.
- Stay within bundle budgets defined in `docs/04-frontend/performance.md`.

## Imports

- Use path aliases: `@/components/...`, `@/features/...`, `@/core/...`, `@/lib/...`.
- Don't import from `core/` into `app/` and back into `core/` (no circular).

## What NOT to do

- Don't put platform-specific code in `core/` (separate rule enforces this).
- Don't create new shadcn components by hand — use the CLI.
- Don't roll your own data fetching when a TanStack hook already exists.
- Don't reinvent compliance / RRB rules — they live in `core/utils/` and `core/constants/`.
- Don't add Tailwind classes inside `core/`.
